item.description:
 &lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PGF&amp;#x2F;Ti&lt;em&gt;k&lt;/em&gt;Z&lt;/strong&gt; is a pair of languages for producing vector graphics (e.g., technical illustrations and drawings) from a geometric&amp;#x2F;algebraic description, with standard features including the drawing of points, lines, arrows, paths, circles, ellipses and polygons.&lt;/p&gt;
